    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text *means* — moving from observation (what does it say?) to discerning the author's intent in his original context. Ruth 4 must be read both as ancient Near Eastern legal narrative and as canonical theology pointing forward to David and, through David, to Christ. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from gate to genealogy.",
